Courts / Tables
In Tournament.app, "courts" refer to the designated playing areas for matches. For table soccer (foosball) tournaments, courts are equivalent to tables. Each court represents a single foosball table where matches are played.

GET
/tournaments/:id/courts
https://api.tournament.io/v1/public/tournaments/:id/courts
This endpoint retrieves a list of courts associated with a specific tournament.

 A court object includes the `currentMatchId` of the currently assigned match, if a match is assigned and announced. Add the query parameter `includeMatchDetails=true` to include the full match.
Parameters
includeMatchDetails
true
When set to `true` the current match on the court will be included in the response. The match object is described in the Matches section.
Headers
Authorization
Your API token
Example request:
Copy to clipboard
curl "https://api.tournament.io/v1/public/tournaments/:id/courts?includeMatchDetails=true" \
  -H 'Authorization: <YOUR_API_TOKEN>' \
  -X GET 
Example response - 200:
[
  {
    "id": "tio:XBZxd1GA3Kog9",
    "number": 1,
    "name": "1"
  },
  {
    "id": "tio:dLUOkXt5oHEvq",
    "number": 2,
    "name": "2",
    "currentMatchId": "tio:dWT5oSbv2kYQg"
  },
  {
    "id": "tio:5k35E1vfm3IwG",
    "number": 3,
    "name": "3"
  },
  ...
]
